                            <comment id="117912" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2015 12:06:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That should be in place in both master and the maintenance branch for Fowler. I got your test cases to work with a few gotchas. &lt;tt&gt;PATCH&lt;/tt&gt; requests don&apos;t return &lt;tt&gt;201 Created&lt;/tt&gt; but &lt;tt&gt;200 OK&lt;/tt&gt; unless response bodies are explicitly turned off.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your second test case is actually sending invalid data as it&apos;s not sending JSON Patch actually. I&apos;ve improved the error message you get for the &lt;tt&gt;400 Bad Request&lt;/tt&gt; to indicate potential format errors.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
